  <section id="projects">
    <h2>Selected Projects</h2>

    <article>
      <h3>Social Networks and Insurance: An Anthropological Approach to Risk Management</h3>
      <p><strong>Date:</strong> Dec 2024 – Apr 2025</p>
      <p>This Master's thesis explores how social networks influence perceptions of insurance and how life events shape coverage decisions. It challenges traditional models by adding cultural context to risk and trust.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Semi-structured interviews & informal conversations</li>
        <li>Comparative literature & industry analysis</li>
        <li><strong>Insights:</strong> Life events are key insurance triggers; trust and culture deeply affect adoption.</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> Introduced cultural and social analysis into industry discussions of consumer behavior.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>UX Research Internship – IF Insurance (Customer Insights Dept.)</h3>
      <p><strong>Date:</strong> Aug 2024 – Jan 2025</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed and led qualitative research to inform product development.</li>
        <li>Created a research repository, conducted internal and competitor analysis.</li>
        <li>Designed customer journey studies and usability tests for insurance webshops.</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> Delivered insights that shaped CX strategy and product improvements.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>KU Lighthouse: Cultural & Operational Analysis</h3>
      <p><strong>Date:</strong> Jan 2024 – Jun 2024</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Ethnographic interviews, observations, and focus groups with staff/students.</li>
        <li>Process mapping and team dynamic evaluation.</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> Revealed visibility, location, and morale issues; offered solutions for organizational improvements.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

